==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Router
<hw>Rout"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Carp.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A plane made like a spokeshave, for
working the inside edges of circular sashes.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
plane with a hooked tool protruding far below the sole, for smoothing
the bottom of a cavity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A machine with a rapidly
revolving vertical spindle and cutter for scooping out the surface of
wood or metal, as between and around the engraved parts of an
electrotype.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Routhe</ent>⟦br⟧
